    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1961-06-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1961-06-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="16"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d16">
                <head>16. Letter From President <persName corresp="#p_KJF2" type="from"
                        >Kennedy</persName> to Chairman <persName corresp="#p_KNS2" type="to"
                        >Khrushchev</persName>
                    <note n="0" type="source" xml:id="d16fn0">Source: Department of State,
                        Presidential Correspondence: Lot 66 D 204. No classification marking.
                        Another copy of this message is in the Kennedy Library, National Security
                        Files, Countries Series, <gloss target="#t_USSR1">USSR</gloss>, <persName
                            corresp="#p_KNS2">Khrushchev</persName> Correspondence.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1961-06-10">June 10, 1961</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Chairman</hi>: Many thanks for your kindness in
                    presenting me with a case of beverages during our recent meeting in Vienna.<note
                        n="1" xml:id="d16fn1">Regarding these meetings June 3-4, see <ref
                            target="frus1961-63v05">volume V</ref>.</note> I would also like to
                    express my appreciation to the Soviet Government for the gold cigar chest,
                    caviar and records. For these courtesies I am very grateful.</p>
                <p>Sincerely,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_KJF2">
                            <hi rend="strong">John F. Kennedy</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                    <note n="2" xml:id="d16fn2">Printed from a copy that indicates the original was
                        signed by President <persName corresp="#p_KRF1">Kennedy</persName>.</note>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
